5
00:00:15,493 --> 00:00:17,053
And it's a privilege to be here today.

6
00:00:18,474 --> 00:00:19,594
So my name is Zach Lowery.

7
00:00:19,654 --> 00:00:22,295
I was the project animation director on Saints Row 4.

8
00:00:23,075 --> 00:00:25,436
And I've been in the industry for about nine years

9
00:00:25,456 --> 00:00:26,297
this past February.

10
00:00:27,097 --> 00:00:27,897
And there we go.

11
00:00:28,884 --> 00:00:33,907
So over the course of those nine years, I've had the luxury of working on the Saints Row franchise.

12
00:00:35,088 --> 00:00:37,870
Every iteration, every box title, every extended content.

13
00:00:39,917 --> 00:00:43,860
And for those who don't know, Saints Row is an open world, third person, action driving

14
00:00:43,940 --> 00:00:47,843
combat game with a fully customizable protagonist.

15
00:00:47,923 --> 00:00:50,365
Saints Row can potentially be an animator's dream come true.

16
00:00:50,706 --> 00:00:54,669
Over the course of the franchise, it's gotten more over the top than almost anything goes.

17
00:00:54,929 --> 00:00:55,590
So it's really fun.

18
00:00:56,570 --> 00:01:01,414
Just to kind of set the tone for some of those over the top experiences that you might have

19
00:01:01,435 --> 00:01:05,698
in a Saints Row game, we've had cyberspace, Tron inspired levels.

20
00:01:06,772 --> 00:01:13,437
Paramilitary luchadors, skydiving gun battles, nine foot tall brute clones, furry mascots

21
00:01:13,457 --> 00:01:16,819
who want to beat you within an inch of your life, driving a car through traffic while

22
00:01:16,839 --> 00:01:21,102
a tiger mauls you from the back seat, missions on Mars, and a gun that shoots a frickin'

23
00:01:21,122 --> 00:01:21,302
shark.

24
00:01:23,006 --> 00:01:25,830
Now, this is only the over-the-top stuff that happened in Saints Row 3.

25
00:01:26,591 --> 00:01:31,658
So when Saints Row 4 was being concepted, the entire team was tasked with one-upping

26
00:01:31,678 --> 00:01:33,621
the over-the-topness of Saints Row 3.

27
00:01:34,042 --> 00:01:36,605
So of course our only response was, holy shit.

28
00:01:38,603 --> 00:01:41,686
So the internet often jokes, where can they take Saints Row next?

29
00:01:42,186 --> 00:01:46,890
Saints Row 1 started and you were an up-and-comer on a street gang and you joined that gang.

30
00:01:46,990 --> 00:01:49,032
Saints Row 2, you went on to run that gang.

31
00:01:49,573 --> 00:01:53,256
Saints Row 3, you had taken that gang to pop culture icon status

32
00:01:53,897 --> 00:01:57,940
and everyone in the city loved you no matter if you were murdering or driving over pedestrians.

33
00:01:58,941 --> 00:02:00,142
So where does it go from there?

34
00:02:00,523 --> 00:02:02,565
It went to the only logical place that it could go.

35
00:02:02,845 --> 00:02:04,867
And that's that you became president of the United States,

36
00:02:05,648 --> 00:02:07,670
aliens kidnapped you because you were the only thing

37
00:02:07,710 --> 00:02:09,632
standing in their way from world domination,

38
00:02:09,992 --> 00:02:12,355
and then you were trapped in a Matrix-inspired simulation

39
00:02:12,395 --> 00:02:13,836
where you were given superpowers.

40
